                                    oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                                    oc:codeContent """---
description: Resilient deployment workflow
---

# Deployment Workflow

Running steps with error handling...

## Step 1: Tests
!`npm test`

if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
  ERROR: Tests failed

  Options:
  1. Fix tests and retry
  2. Skip tests (NOT recommended)
  3. Abort deployment

  What would you like to do?

  [Wait for user input before continuing]
fi

## Step 2: Build
[Continue only if Step 1 succeeded]
""" ;
                                    oc:codeLanguage "markdown" ;
                                    oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                                    oc:sourceLocation "lines 521-548" ] ;
                            oc:sectionLevel 3 ;
                            oc:sectionOrder 22 ;
                            oc:sectionTitle "Graceful Failure" ],
                        [ a oc:Section ;
                            oc:hasContent [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                                    oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                                    oc:codeContent """---
description: Workflow with checkpoints
---

# Multi-Stage Deployment

## Checkpoint 1: Validation
!`validate.sh`
echo "checkpoint:validation" >> .claude/deployment-checkpoints.log

## Checkpoint 2: Build
!`build.sh`
echo "checkpoint:build" >> .claude/deployment-checkpoints.log

## Checkpoint 3: Deploy
!`deploy.sh`
echo "checkpoint:deploy" >> .claude/deployment-checkpoints.log

If any step fails, resume with:
/deployment-resume [last-successful-checkpoint]
""" ;
                                    oc:codeLanguage "markdown" ;
                                    oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                                    oc:sourceLocation "lines 581-602" ] ;
                            oc:sectionLevel 3 ;
                            oc:sectionOrder 24 ;
                            oc:sectionTitle "Checkpoint Recovery" ],
                        [ a oc:Section ;
                            oc:hasContent [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                                    oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                                    oc:codeContent """---
description: Deployment with rollback
---

# Deploy with Rollback

Saving current state for rollback...
Previous version: !`current-version.sh`

Deploying new version...

!`deploy.sh`

if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
  DEPLOYMENT FAILED

  Initiating automatic rollback...
  !`rollback.sh`

  Rolled back to previous version.
  Check logs for failure details.
fi

Deployment complete.
""" ;
